<i>noun</i>: 훼방 [훼ː방], 폭동 [폭똥], 소요 [소요], 소란 [소란], 소동 [소동], 분탕질 [분탕질], 분란 [불란], 방해 [방해], 동요 [동ː요], 난동 [난ː동], 교란 [교란], 거리낌 [거리낌] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훼방 [훼ː방]</dt><br>
<dd>1. slander; libel</dd><br>
<dd>남을 해치려고 나쁘게 말함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of speaking ill of another to do harm to him/her.</dd><br>
<dd>2. interruption; disturbance; obstruction</dd><br>
<dd>남의 일을 방해함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of interrupting another's affair.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>폭동 [폭똥]</dt><br>
<dd>riot; uprising; disturbance</dd><br>
<dd>여러 사람이 집단으로 폭력 행위를 일으켜 사회를 어지럽게 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of many people, as a group, starting violence and causing confusion in society.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>소요 [소요]</dt><br>
<dd>disturbance; commotion; agitation; riot</dd><br>
<dd>여러 사람이 시끄럽게 들고일어남. 또는 그런 소란.</dd><br>
<dd>A loud protest caused by a group of people, or such a disturbance.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>소란 [소란]</dt><br>
<dd>disturbance; fuss; commotion</dd><br>
<dd>시끄럽고 정신없게 복잡함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being noisy and hectic.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>소동 [소동]</dt><br>
<dd>disturbance; fuss; commotion</dd><br>
<dd>시끄럽게 떠들고 어지럽게 행동하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of making a loud noise and causing a commotion.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>분탕질 [분탕질]</dt><br>
<dd>1. squandering; dissipating</dd><br>
<dd>집안의 재산을 모두 없애 버리는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of wastefully spending all of a household's wealth.</dd><br>
<dd>2. disturbance; commotion</dd><br>
<dd>시끄럽게 떠들며 소동을 일으키는 짓.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of causing a loud, noisy commotion.</dd><br>
<dd>3. robbery</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 쳐들어가서 재물을 빼앗거나 훔치는 짓.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) The act of invading and taking or stealing others' property.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>분란 [불란]</dt><br>
<dd>disorder; disturbance</dd><br>
<dd>문제가 생겨서 시끄럽게 다투거나 떠들썩함.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being in a noisy argument or conflict due to some trouble.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>방해 [방해]</dt><br>
<dd>distraction; getting in one's way; disturbance</dd><br>
<dd>일이 제대로 되지 못하도록 간섭하고 막음.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of interfering and hindering work from being done properly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>동요 [동ː요]</dt><br>
<dd>1. tremble; shake</dd><br>
<dd>물체가 이리저리 흔들림.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which an object is shaken all about.</dd><br>
<dd>2. restlessness</dd><br>
<dd>생각이나 마음이 정해지지 않고 자꾸 달라짐.</dd><br>
<dd>An opinion or mind continuing to change without being fixed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. agitation; disturbance</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 제도나 상황이 안정되지 않아 혼란스러움.</dd><br>
<dd>A confusion from an instability in a system or situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>난동 [난ː동]</dt><br>
<dd>violent acts; wild behavior; disturbance</dd><br>
<dd>질서를 어지럽히며 멋대로 행동함. 또는 그런 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>Acting as one pleases, disrupting public order, or this behavior.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>교란 [교란]</dt><br>
<dd>confusion; disturbance; bewilderment</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 체계의 질서나 사람의 마음을 뒤흔들어 어지럽게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of disturbing the order of a system or a person's mind to cause confusion.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>거리낌 [거리낌]</dt><br>
<dd>1. trouble; disturbance; obstacle</dd><br>
<dd>일하거나 행동하는 데에 걸려서 방해가 되는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>Things that get in the way of doing something or acting.</dd><br>
<dd>2. hesitation; reluctance; inhibition</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 마음에 걸리고 꺼려짐.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being troubled by something and reluctant to do it.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>